Describe an interesting building you have seen
- where it is
- what it looks like
- what it is used for
- explain why you think it is interesting

I’d like to talk about Landmark 81, which is the tallest skyscraper in Vietnam and one of the most impressive buildings I’ve ever seen.

It’s located in Ho Chi Minh City, right by the Saigon River, so it really stands out in the skyline, especially from a distance. I remember the first time I saw it in person—I was honestly quite amazed by how tall and modern it looked.

In terms of appearance, it’s a very striking building. The design is inspired by a bundle of bamboo, which symbolizes strength in Vietnamese culture. The entire exterior is covered in glass, so it reflects the sunlight during the day, and at night, it lights up beautifully with LED displays. I actually went there in the evening once, and the view was absolutely stunning.

As for its function, it’s a multi-purpose complex. The lower floors are used as a large shopping mall with lots of restaurants and entertainment options. The middle section consists of luxury apartments, and the upper floors include a five-star hotel and an observation deck where visitors can see the whole city from above. When I visited the observation deck, I spent quite a while just looking at the city lights—it was a really memorable experience.

What makes this building so interesting to me is not just its height, but what it represents. I think it’s a symbol of how quickly Vietnam is developing and becoming more modern. Every time I see it, I feel quite proud, and it reminds me of how much the city has changed over the years.
